FullDescriptions:
The National Abortion Federation (NAF), the leading pro-choice organization representing abortion providers and their patients, has an immediate full-time opening for the position of Database Administrator.
NAF is a 501(c)(3) organization, dedicated to ensuring that abortion is safe, legal, and accessible. Our members include clinics, hospitals and physicians’ offices in the United States, Canada, Mexico City, and Colombia. Our dynamic and innovative programs span a wide range of services designed to meet the unique needs of abortion providers and their patients.
The CRM System Administrator will work closely with all departments to ensure the Customer Relationship Management system works effectively across the organization. This role will participate in planning, organizing and management of all CRM projects to ensure effective operations; identify areas for improvement and develop technical improvement plans; work with vendor partners to design, configure, test and deploy changes to CRM database workflows; and design, develop and implement key reports using available tools.
Additionally, this role will assist the Communications and Membership teams and Development to analyze and report campaign effectiveness including traffic, acquisition, conversion, retention and revenue. The CRM System Administrator will stay informed on current as well as new and emerging CRM features, roadmaps and releases, while maintaining the system security including sharing rules and security levels. The CRM System Administrator will report to the Information Security and Strategy Specialist and will work closely with the leaders of NAF’s departments, and will regularly interact with staff.
Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
 Manage the creation, retiring, and support of user accounts;
 Manage the CRM platform and architecture to ensure seamless operation across the organization;
 Use customer journey mapping to maximize member/donor experience.
 Work closely with all departments ensure the CRM works effectively and to create standardized database policies, SOPs, and system documentation for our internal CRM and members-only data systems;
 Oversee and maintain the integrity and quality of NAF’s data;
 Stay current on enhancements to CRM and facilitate (and in some cases provide) user training;
 Collaborate across teams to draft, document and execute testing plans for system upgrades, and changes;
 Design and execute customized, regular, and ad-hoc reports, queries, and lists;
 Perform periodic data enhancement, data hygiene and archiving projects;
 Collaborate with staff to generate financial, analytical, statistical, and demographic reports, as well as mailing lists and other data extractions as requested;
 Provide onboarding, training as well as ongoing timely and friendly “customer support” to staff and help them troubleshoot data issues as needed;
 Investigate and resolve any problems related to database functions.
Qualifications:
 Strong commitment to reproductive choice;
 3+ years of non-profit database experience; specific experience with NetForum (or other Abila or Community Brands products) not required but strongly preferred;
 Strong experience with, and knowledge of, database best practices;
 Detail oriented and extremely well organized while able to understand and apply big-picture concepts;
 Strong written and oral communications skills;
 Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously with a high level of autonomy and independence;
 Flexibility and adaptable personality to handle shifting needs, evolving priorities and urgent situations that arise;
 Excellent time management skills and an ability to work in a deadline-driven environment;
 Ability to collaborate across teams with strong interpersonal skills;
 Strong interpersonal skills, with demonstrated ability to work across teams, as well as independently; and
 Strong Microsoft Office proficiency.
Compensation:
Salary is commensurate with qualifications and experience. Excellent benefits. Position is located in Washington, DC.
The National Abortion Federation is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer.
If there is interest in your application materials for this position, you will be contacted by a member of our organization. No phone calls, please.

